
5. Esoteric

Use cases: vision talks, philosophy, storytelling, branding, keynotes
Design intent

Atmosphere, drama, symbolism.
Font rules

    Titles: Serif, bold or display-like
    (LiberationSerif-Bold)

    Body: Sans or serif, sparse
    (LiberationSans-Regular)

    Quotes: Serif italic, emphasized

Color rules

    Bright: parchment / rose / sand

    Dark: deep purple, crimson, midnight blue

    Accents: gold, violet, blood red

Layout & spacing

    Large title spacing

    Centered text more often

    Strong visual pauses

    Fewer elements per slide

XSS characteristics

    Large margins

    High title-to-body contrast

    Decorative color blocks allowed










1. Academic

Use cases: lectures, papers, conferences, teaching, research
Design intent

Readable for long sessions, printable, conservative, timeless.
Font rules

    Titles: Serif, bold
    (LiberationSerif-Bold)

    Body: Serif, regular
    (LiberationSerif-Regular)

    Code: Monospace, neutral
    (LiberationMono-Regular)

    Quotes: Serif italic

Color rules

    Bright: white / ivory background, dark gray text

    Dark: near-black background, warm off-white text

    Accents are low saturation (gray, muted blue, muted green)

Layout & spacing

    Centered main title

    Left-aligned paragraphs

    Moderate margins

    Minimal backgrounds on titles (or very light gray)

XSS characteristics

    Smaller contrast jumps

    No strong accent blocks

    Comfortable font sizes (not aggressive)


2. Technical

Use cases: engineering talks, APIs, architecture, code-heavy demos
Design intent

Clarity, precision, neutrality, zero ornamentation.
Font rules

    Titles: Neutral sans, bold
    (NotoSans-Bold)

    Body: Neutral sans
    (NotoSans-Regular)

    Code: Modern mono
    (NotoSansMono-Regular)

Color rules

    Bright: light blue / cool gray background

    Dark: blue-black / graphite background

    Accents: blue, cyan, teal

    Code blocks clearly separated

Layout & spacing

    Strict left alignment for text

    Centered main title only

    Tighter margins than academic

    Clear block separation

XSS characteristics

    Strong code contrast

    Consistent block widths

    Minimal decorative padding


3. Friendly

Use cases: onboarding, community talks, product intros, workshops
Design intent

Approachable, warm, human, non-intimidating.
Font rules

    Titles: Humanist sans, bold
    (DejaVuSans-Bold)

    Body: Humanist sans
    (DejaVuSans-Regular)

    Code: Same family mono
    (DejaVuSansMono-Regular)

Color rules

    Bright: warm off-white, pastel backgrounds

    Dark: deep brown / warm charcoal

    Accents: orange, coral, mint

Layout & spacing

    More vertical breathing room

    Slightly larger fonts

    Rounded-looking blocks (via padding)

    Centered titles, relaxed paragraph margins

XSS characteristics

    Larger padding values

    Softer contrast

    Visually “open” layout


4. Technical-Minimal

Use cases: dashboards, system diagrams, status reports

(This is distinct from “Technical”: more minimal, more UI-like)
Design intent

Functional, compact, distraction-free.
Font rules

    Titles: Sans, medium-to-bold
    (LiberationSans-Bold)

    Body: Sans, regular
    (LiberationSans-Regular)

    Code: Compact mono
    (LiberationMono-Regular)

Color rules

    Bright: pure white + gray lines

    Dark: near-black + gray text

    Accents: single color only (blue or green)

Layout & spacing

    Tight vertical rhythm

    Small margins

    Mostly left-aligned

    Narrow content widths

XSS characteristics

    Small padding

    Subtle borders

    High information density
